OL,3,CVennells: Claims post office had
OL,4,C'driven subpostmaster to suicide...
OL,5,Cunhelpful'
OL,7,FJason Beer KC asked: "You say in your
OL,8,Fstatement that 'this was a time of
OL,9,Fgreat distress for Mr Griffiths's
OL,10,Ffamily, and I felt the accusations of
OL,11,Fblame were unhelpful'... is that right
OL,12,Fthat you felt that Mr Bates's
OL,13,Faccusations of blame were unhelpful?"
OL,15,FMs Vennells responded: "I think at
OL,16,Fthis stage some of those accusations
OL,17,Fof blame were unhelpful, yes, because
OL,18,Fthe Post Office needed to respond to
OL,19,Fthis properly and at that stage, I had
OL,20,Fno understanding as to what had gone
OL,21,Fon."
