OL,5,Cunhelpful'
OL,7,FMs Vennells also broke down in tears
OL,8,Fas she discussed Mr Griffiths and a
OL,9,Fprevious experience of a Post Office
OL,10,Fcolleague taking their own life.
OL,12,FThe inquiry was shown an email from Mr
OL,13,FBates to Ms Vennells and others in
OL,14,Fwhich Mr Bates said he had received an
OL,15,Femail from a relative of Mr Griffiths
OL,16,Fthe day he walked in front of a bus
OL,17,Fand was in hospital, and the relative
OL,18,Fsaid "the Post Office had driven him
OL,19,Fto suicide".
